Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "sledi" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted with a star and English translations in parenthesis:

1. *Sledi* nam težak zadatak da završimo projekat na vreme. (We have a difficult task *ahead* of us to finish the project on time.)
2. U sledećoj nedelji *sledi* nam sastanak s klijentom. (We have a meeting with the client *coming up* next week.)
3. Šta *sledi* nakon ovoga? (What *comes next* after this?)
4. Planirali smo da idemo na izlet sledećeg vikenda, ali sada *sledi* kiša. (We planned to go on a trip next weekend, but now *we're expecting* rain.)
5. Sledeća stanica je Beograd. (*Next* stop is Belgrade.)
6. *Slediš* li me? (Are you *following* me?)
7. Nismo sigurni šta *sledi* posle ovoga, ali ćemo se pripremiti za sve mogućnosti. (We're not sure what *will happen* after this, but we'll be prepared for all possibilities.)
8. Kada pogledate u prošlost, *sledi* vam da razmislite o budućnosti. (When you look back, *it's natural to think* about the future.)
9. Sledeći put kada dođeš, obavezno mi se javi. (*Next time* you come, be sure to let me know.)
10. U ovom trenutku, *sledi* nam da se fokusiramo na rešavanje problema. (At this moment, *we need to focus* on solving the problem.)

I hope these examples help!